snippet: Ireland’s economy is growing at a rapid pace last experienced at the tail end of the Celtic Tiger boom, government statisticians reported on Thursday.
abstract: Government statistics show that Ireland's economy is growing at a rapid pace; Ireland's gross domestic product grew 7.7 percent between July 2013 and June 2014, biggest annual rate of growth since early 2007.
lead_paragraph: Ireland’s economy is growing at a rapid pace last experienced at the tail end of the Celtic Tiger boom, government statisticians reported on Thursday.

headline.main: Economy in Ireland Continues to Grow
headline.print_headline: Economy in Ireland Continues to Grow
